{"questionId":"9069619","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Ammonium nitrate, NH<sub>4</sub>NO<sub>3</sub>, is used as a high nitrogen fertilizer.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Cold packs contain ammonium nitrate and water separated by a membrane.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>The change in enthalpy when ammonium nitrate dissolves in water is&nbsp;25.69 kJ mol<sup>−1</sup>. Determine the mass of ammonium nitrate in the cold pack using&nbsp;your answer obtained in (e)(i) and section 6 of the data booklet.</p>\n<p>If you did not obtain an answer in (e)(i), use 3.11 × 10<sup>3</sup> J, although this is not the correct answer.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p>«<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>58</mn><mo>×</mo><msup><mn>10</mn><mn>3</mn></msup><mo> </mo><mi>J</mi><mo>×</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo> </mo><mi>k</mi><mi>J</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>1000</mn><mo> </mo><mi>J</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>×</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>1</mn><mo> </mo><mi>m</mi><mi>o</mi><mi>l</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>25</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>69</mn><mo> </mo><mi>k</mi><mi>J</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo></math>» <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>100</mn></math> «mol» ✔</p>\n<p>«<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>100</mn></math> mol&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>×</mo><mo> </mo><mn>80</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>06</mn></math> g mol<sup>−1</sup> =»&nbsp;8.01 «g» ✔</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em>Award <strong>[2]</strong> for the correct final answer.</em></p>\n<p><em>Accept range of</em> <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn mathvariant=\"italic\">8</mn><mo mathvariant=\"italic\">.</mo><mn mathvariant=\"italic\">00</mn><mo mathvariant=\"italic\">&nbsp;</mo><mo mathvariant=\"italic\">–</mo><mo mathvariant=\"italic\">&nbsp;</mo><mn mathvariant=\"italic\">8</mn><mo mathvariant=\"italic\">.</mo><mn mathvariant=\"italic\">10</mn></math> <em>«g»</em>.</p>\n<p><em>If</em> <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn mathvariant=\"italic\">3</mn><mo mathvariant=\"italic\">.</mo><mn mathvariant=\"italic\">11</mn><mo mathvariant=\"italic\">&nbsp;</mo><mo mathvariant=\"italic\">×</mo><mo mathvariant=\"italic\">&nbsp;</mo><msup><mn mathvariant=\"italic\">10</mn><mn mathvariant=\"italic\">3</mn></msup></math> <em>J</em> <em>used then answer is</em> <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn mathvariant=\"italic\">9</mn><mo mathvariant=\"italic\">.</mo><mn mathvariant=\"italic\">69</mn></math> <em>«g».</em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"9069619","referenceCode":"22N.2.sl.TZ0.e.ii","subjectId":"45-dp-chemistry-last-assessment-2024","title":"The change in enthalpy when ammonium nitrate dissolves in water is 25.69 kJ mol−1. Determine the mass of ammonium nitrate in the cold pack using your answer obtained in (e)(i) and ","paper":"2","level":"SL","questionNumber":"e.ii","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Core","Core","Topic 5: Energetics/thermochemistry","5.1 Measuring energy changes","Core","Topic 5: Energetics/thermochemistry"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}